{"title":"Welcome","markdown":{"headingText":"Welcome","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":["unnumbered"],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\nThis book is a practical guide for working with data related to the field of\nthermal ecology using R. It focuses specifically on the processes and challenges \nyou'll face with such data.\n\n```{r}\n#| include: false\n#| message: false\n#| warning: false\n\n\nlibrary(gh)\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nlibrary(lubridate)\nlibrary(stringr)\n\n#releases <- gh(\"GET /repos/AtlasOfLivingAustralia/cleaning_data/releases\", \n#   owner = \"AtlasOfLivingAustralia\",\n#   repo = \"cleaning_data\")\n\n#release_number <- releases[[1]][[\"tag_name\"]] |>\n#  stringr::str_sub(start = 2) # remove \"v\"\n\ndate_rendered <- lubridate::today() %>%\n  lubridate::stamp(\"1 March, 1999\")()\n\n```\n\n\n**This book was last rendered on `{r} date_rendered`.**\n\n## 1. Environmental Data\n\nLearn how to load and clean raw data from own data loggers, access climate databases and microclimate simulations, and calculating metrics of heatwaves.\n\n- Own data loggers\n\n- Climatology database\n\n- Microclimate database\n\n- Detecting heatwaves/cold spells\n\n## 2. Physiological Data\n\n- Thermal performance curves\n\n- Respirometry\n\n- Thermal-death-time curves\n\n- Q10s and rates of change\n\n\n## 3. Behavioural Data\n\n- Torpor/arousal patterns\n\n- Thermal images\n\n- Thermoregulation\n\n\n## 4. Comparative Data\n\n- Effect sizes\n\n- Comparative analysis\n\n- Scaling relationships\n\n\n## 5. Simulation\n\n- Operative temeprature models\n\n- Dynamic Energy Budget\n\n\n## 6. Other\n\n- Repeatability \n\n\n## Acknowledgements\n\nThis book was inspired by the [Cleaning Biodiversity Data in R](https://cleaning-data-r.ala.org.au/) book. This book is a collaborative effort by members of the [Thermal Ecology Alliance](https://www.thermalecologyalliance.org/).\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-forma